                            A Pennsylvania businessman who had Tom Homan on his payroll led companies to believe his connections to the future border czar could help advance their bids for government work, industry executives said.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
                        <span class="story-card__byline-author">
                by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/avi-asher-schapiro">Avi Asher-Schapiro</a>, <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/jeff-ernsthausen">Jeff Ernsthausen</a> and <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/mica-rosenberg">Mica Rosenberg</a>,
            </span>
                        <span class="story-card__byline-dateline">
                <time class="timestamp" datetime="2025-10-01EDT12:00">Oct. 1, 2025, 12 p.m. EDT</time>
            </span>
        </p>

            </div>
</div>
